Losing my best friend has been one the hardest things ive ever had to go through & I haven’t really known how to feel about it all, what I do know is I want to use my platform to do some good & spread as much awareness about mens mental health & male suicide as I can. 

I’ve been thinking over & over what can I do for joe, how can I keep his memory alive & make what he went through & what we’ve experienced help others.

I hope you can all get onboard this journey with me & we can make a difference to how men deal with their mental health. I’m ready to talk & I want others to be too, and I will challenge myself month in month out to make that happen, I just need your support to raise funds & give @birminghammind the opportunity to make a difference. 

This, is for joe.

I set myself a goal to be the fittest I've been & I right now feel healthy and strong. 

I got some challenges to do & some goals to reach.

Turning 32 on Sunday & over the last year I've realised training for aesthetics only wasn't right for me going forward. I wanted to feel healthy as possible so the switch up in training style has helped me not only physically but mentally too. 

Especially days where I feel riddled with anxiety I go in and work at high intensity for 30-45 mins and I push myself to a point where I look like I've just got out the shower. The anxiety just seems to calm down and I start my day off right. 

Just get in the gym and get it done and push yourself to your limit for 30/45 mins. 

@gymking fuelling the training as always 👊🏼

So my 31st year was one of the best years of my life. ✌🏽💙👶🏼 let's see what my 32nd year brings me.
